00:51:24.070 --> 00:51:27.990
of those lost notes ever existed or
not, because if you think about --

00:51:27.990 --> 00:51:30.270
for example, I think particularly
if you read a wonderful book

00:51:30.270 --> 00:51:37.270
by Joanne Freeman on the 1790s, you
realize how much this was a period

00:51:37.270 --> 00:51:40.150
where people made assertions,
and then wanted to claim

00:51:40.150 --> 00:51:42.860
that they had paper to back it up.

00:51:42.860 --> 00:51:46.650
So, you know, who knows how
much the notes are about that.

00:51:46.650 --> 00:51:48.730
But there are notes
that we know exist

00:51:48.730 --> 00:51:53.200
that are missing the original Yates
notes are much of Lansing's copy

00:51:53.200 --> 00:51:55.950
of those have never been found.

00:51:55.950 --> 00:52:01.550
Jim Hutson found a very
