00:52:03.950 --> 00:52:08.450
So we're dealing with
multiple conflicting accounts.

00:52:08.450 --> 00:52:10.830
One thing that I think
my book disagrees

00:52:10.830 --> 00:52:12.480
with is what people have taken

00:52:12.480 --> 00:52:16.250 position:56%
as they've made Madison's notes
always the stable objective account.

00:52:16.250 --> 00:52:21.120
And then every time that Madison's
version, particularly of himself,

00:52:21.120 --> 00:52:25.090
disagreed with anybody
else, they picked Madison.

00:52:25.090 --> 00:52:28.970
My book tries to argue that
on a couple of the issues

00:52:28.970 --> 00:52:31.820
that people disagreed with, there
were reasons why Madison later

00:52:31.820 --> 00:52:35.380
on wanted to say that he
hadn't said those things.

00:52:35.380 --> 00:52:37.430
And I'm more agnostic.

00:52:37.430 --> 00:52:40.600
Madison was very close to
Hamilton during the Convention.

00:52:40.600 --> 00:52:43.690
And when Jefferson comes back,

00:52:43.690 --> 00:52:46.670
Jefferson does not think
Hamilton is a good guy,

00:52:46.670 --> 00:52:49.070
and Madison distances himself.

00:52:49.070 --> 00:52:51.410
And so the book tries
to tell the notes

00:52:51.410 --> 00:52:53.320
and the multiple accounts
out of that history.

00:52:53.320 --> 00:52:55.620
[ Silence ]

00:52:55.620 --> 00:52:56.920
