00:56:21.110 --> 00:56:22.710
on Madison as president.

00:56:22.710 --> 00:56:27.170
And one of the things that I
think Wills does very well is talk

00:56:27.170 --> 00:56:30.660
about how we don't give
Madison enough credit

00:56:30.660 --> 00:56:35.230
for successfully navigating
through the War of 1812.

00:56:35.230 --> 00:56:38.200
And I think in that
sense, he's a nationalist.

00:56:38.200 --> 00:56:41.340
In that sense, right, Jefferson
we know makes the same --

00:56:41.340 --> 00:56:42.640
you know, it's one thing
before you're president,

00:56:42.640 --> 00:56:43.940
and then it's another thing
after you're president.

00:56:43.940 --> 00:56:45.240
So I think he would not have --

00:56:45.240 --> 00:56:46.540 position:56%
how he would have done that would he
have been a constitutional unionist,

00:56:46.540 --> 00:56:47.840
who knows?

00:56:47.840 --> 00:56:49.140
But personally, I would have
put him on the union side.

00:56:49.140 --> 00:56:50.440
He would have had to move to West
Virginia, though, in order to --

00:56:50.440 --> 00:56:51.740
[laughter] maybe wouldn't
have left Montpelier.

